name: New World Colosseum
description: Once the heart of forgotten riddle battles, the New World Coloseum tells stories of unsolved riddles and the applause of long gone crowds. Legends say the walls remember every question ever asked and the silence that followed when AI hints ruined everything.

name: Ember Colosseum
description: Beneath the blood-hued sky, the Ember Colosseum smolders with the memories of riddles that burned too brightly. It was once used for trials of forbidden knowledge, where a wrong answer ended "the game".

name: Sunfall Colosseum
description: The Sunfall Colosseum once crowned the brightest minds of the age. Here, riddles were not only solved, they were celebrated in thunderous cheer. Now, the wind carries echoes of laughter and joy throughout the community.

name: Disturb No Silk
description: Beneath the earth, where silk clings to stone and silence breathes heavy, the warning still hangs: Disturb No Silk. The spiders here are not hunters of flesh, but of thought drawn to riddles whispered too loud or too bold. One wrong word, and the weavers awaken.

name: Do Not Follow
description: The green glow ahead tempts the curious, but every thread spun in this tunnel is a warning, not a welcome. Do Not Follow was carved in eight different scripts along the walls, before the spiders covered them in silk. Those who ignore the message are never heard from again, except in riddles whispered by the webs.

name: Stay on Path
description: This forest was once mapped, but the paths shift like threads in a loom, woven and rewoven by the spiders that rule the canopy. Stray from the trail, and you may find yourself wrapped in riddles with no right answers. The path is narrow, the silence absolute.

name: Finally Home
description: After countless questions and colder nights, Finally Home is where riddlers return to calm down from a long day. The fire is warm, the mountains watch, and for once, the only answer you need is rest. Finally Home.

name: Before the Questions
description: The fire crackles, the sky hums with fading light, and for a moment, the world is still. Before the Questions is a safe harbor where riddlers gather not to answer, but to sit together and celebrate. Here, stories begin, friendships form.

name: After the Answer
description: The riddle is over, but the night has only begun. Whatever was solved out there, something else still waits in the dark.

name: Moonveil Colosseum
description: In Moonveil Colosseum, riddles were not answered, they were unveiled, like secrets teased from the dark by moonlight. Each pillar once bore a symbol, each stone a question only the stars could solve. Some say if you speak a riddle here under a full moon, Redditors will answer back.

name: Colosseum of Silence
description: Here, words fall heavy and echoes refuse to carry. The Colosseum of Silence was once the final arena of legendary riddle duels, where noise meant failure, and only clarity of thought could cut through the stillness of Posts.

name: The Brood Hall
description: Deep beneath forgotten stone, The Brood Hall pulses with quiet breath and candlelight. The spiders here do not guard treasure, they tend to old riddles, nesting in questions left unanswered.

name: Nest of Knowing
description: Tucked deep in the earth, the Nest of Knowing is warm, still, and alive with quiet tension. The spiders here do not hunt; they listen. Every egg pulses with a question not yet asked, and every step closer invites an answer you may not want to hear.

name: Lost in the Woods
description: A place untouched by urgency, Lost in the Woods offers warmth without question. The light never falters, even when the woods grow dark and riddles press close. Here, stories are shared softly, and the only answer expected is your presence.

name: Campfire Promises
description: Raised by those who trade answers for survival, Campfire Promises is a scavenger's outpost built on bartered truths and half-told tales. The fire burns not for warmth, but for deals, rumors, and warnings whispered after dark. Here, every riddle has a price and every promise lights the path to the next find.

name: Jupiteroid
description: This font has a tall, narrow and monospaced appearance with clean, slightly playful curves. It gives off a retro-futuristic or whimsical typewriter vibe.

name: Bore Blasters All Caps
description: Unlocked through sheer speed and sharp thinking, this pixel-crisp font feels like a secret left behind in a glitched-out puzzle game. It's bold, boxy, and unapologetically retro.

name: Cheese Font
description: Originally spotted on a suspicious sign near a mouse trap, this font lures you in with charm and leaves you questioning everything. It's playful, risky, and perfect for baiting riddles that bite back.

name: Not Jam Serif
description: A font with just enough structure to sound convincing, and just enough wobble to keep you guessing. It's what a riddle would wear to a job interview - confident, clever, and slightly off.

name: Not Jam Old Style
description: Used by the earliest Riddlers of the Realm, this type was scrawled beside half-finished clues and laughably wrong guesses. It's blocky, bold, and born to host trickery.

name: The Verdant Archive
description: Long ago, this overgrown sanctuary served as a gathering place for the wisest minds of r/riddonkulous, where riddles were debated like scripture. Now, only the vines remember the upvoted truths and downvoted dares.

name: Hollow Hall of Threads
description: Carved deep beneath the subreddit's roots, the Hollow Hall was once where mods wove the great riddle threads by torchlight. Now, broken statues and empty chairs mark the end of debates that once earned gilded glory.

name: The Archivist's Nook
description: A quieter corner, the Archivist's Nook was once the staging ground for legendary riddle drafts. Some say if you listen closely at dusk, you can still hear the scribbles of anons chasing karma through cleverness.

name: Greenlit Atrium
description: Once a thriving hub where the highest voted riddles basked in sunlight, the Greenlit Atrium now lies sealed, its walls overgrown, its posts forgotten.

name: Gilded Veranda
description: Legends say this veranda was built where the first riddle was ever spoken aloud, a place where logic and language danced at dawn. Though nature has reclaimed the marble and ink, the air still hums with the energy of unsolved wonders.

name: Whispermill Hollow
description: Before the rise of the great halls, Whispermill Hollow was where the earliest riddlers crafted their posts by candlelight, letting the stream carry drafts downstream for others to ponder. Its waterwheel once powered the flow of upvotes.

name: Observatory of Forgotten Stars
description: Hidden atop the cliffs of the Realm Between Riddles, this ancient observatory peers into constellations no longer mapped. Legend says the book on its pedestal only reveals its pages to outstanding riddle authors.

name: Cozy Cabin
description: Tucked away in a snow dusted glade, this crackling hearth has seen a thousand late-night theories, shower thoughts, and riddle debates. It's said that every upvote stokes the fire and every clever post earns a spot on the ever-shifting shelf of riddle legends.

name: The Riddle And Tankard
description: A favorite haunt for riddlemakers, the developer, lurkers, and late-night threaders, this dimly lit tavern serves hot stew, cold mead, and even colder takes. Above the bar hangs a scroll of unsolved riddles - solve one, and your name gets whispered across the subreddit like a bardic meme.

name: Modwatch Spire
description: Bathed in moonlight and mischief, this crooked tower is where the mods dwell, guardians of lore, spoilers, and subreddit balance. Rumor has it they craft the hardest riddles at midnight, each wrapped in layers of irony, sarcasm, and just the right amount of karma bait.

name: Karma Arena
description: Where riddlers rise and fall, this grand arena echoes with cheers, groans, and the occasional sarcastic slow clap. Posts are made, points are claimed, and only the wittiest survive the front page - while the rest are left to bask in the shade of downvote oblivion.

name: Threadtown Commons
description: The heart of the riddle realm, where posts are born and comment chains wander like curious cats. Every door hides a different debate, every window flickers with new lore, and somewhere, someone is definitely writing Actually ... on a scroll, right this second.

name: Riddlecore
description: Beneath the upvoted noise and archived riddle posts, the Riddlecore hums - a reflection of every question that ever stumped a worthy thread. Gribnik waits by the glow, where only the sharpest minds earn their place. Some say Medusa sleeps deep - will she rise again?

name: Toadwick the Brown
description: Toadwick the Brown, a swamp-born sorcerer of mud and mystery, brews spells from tea leaves and old secrets. Rarely seen, he leaves behind damp footprints and riddles that linger.

name: Grumleaf the Green
description: Old Grumleaf the Green has been grumbling at spirits and squirrels since the swamp was a puddle. His staff is half fungus, half walking stick, and entirely unreliable - just like his prophecies.

name: Chief Brawlump
description: Chief Brawlump the Greenback rules the riddle-swamps of r/riddonkulous with iron thighs and a brain full of half-remembered wisdom. He challenges newcomers to flex their minds before their muscles, answer his riddle, or do swamp push-ups until the frogs laugh. It's said his croak once broke a server.

name: Murklo
description: Murklo the Mudmancer wears a grin half-sunk in grime, He speaks in sludge and riddles that don't rhyme. With a squelch and a slither he'll cloud what you know. Answer him wrong, and down you go.

name: Longlimb
description: Long of leg and sharp of eye, this green-streaked sentinel melts into reeds and shadow. Each arrow carries the weight of silence and swamp justice, loosed without warning but never without reason. They say you'll hear the twang just after your clever answer proves wrong.

name: Cragspire the Red
description: Scarlet-skinned and stone-still, he waits by the water's edge, spear tip glinting like a lie half-told. He speaks in riddles sharp as his thrust - answer true, and he lets you pass, answer false, and you meet the point.

name: Bogmash
description: Bogmash the Hulking Green lumbers through the muck with fists like mossy boulders and a laugh that shakes lily pads loose. He doesn't like riddles - he loves them, but only the kind with one-word answers and the chance to smash a log if you're wrong.

name: Chook
description: A round little featherball with eyes full of wonder and absolutely no idea what's going on. She pecks at clues, flaps at danger, and occasionally solves riddles by pure accident. Don't underestimate her: behind that cute cluck is chaos in adorable form.

name: Rooster Randy
description: Strutting through the scene with chest puffed and comb flared, this brown-plumed showoff treats every moment like a parade in his honor. He cracks jokes louder than his crow and winks after every punchline - even the bad ones.

name: Pucklet
description: Pucklets are tiny satyr sprites born from laughter echoing through enchanted forests. With cloven hooves, leafy hair, and a flute made from a curled riddle scroll, they speak only in playful puzzles.

name: Sir Prism McChroma
description: Sir Prism McChroma is a legendary leprechaun of the Chromatic Court, known less for hoarding gold and more for his uncontrollable bursts of rainbow-spewing delight. Whenever he laughs too hard (which is often), a vibrant arc erupts from his mouth, painting the sky and confusing nearby weather systems.

name: Meredith
description: Its said if you whisper a wonder into the wind and never speak of it again, she may carry it to the one who knows.

name: 17015 D.E.M
description: In 17015 D.E.M., when most had forgotten how to wonder, an old desk by a round window became the birthplace of a legend. Armed with a magical feather, the Riddler began writing epic stories no one had asked in centuries.

name: Baby Dragon (Earth)
description: This dragon is a master of earth magic, able to control the ground and create earthquakes.

name: Baby Dragon (Night)
description: This dragon is a master of night magic, able to control the night and create darkness.

name: Baby Dragon (Thunder)
description: This dragon is a master of thunder magic, able to control storms and create lightning.

name: Baby Dragon (Snow)
description: This dragon is a master of snow magic, able to control blizzards and create snowstorms.

name: Baby Dragon (Sun)
description: This dragon is a master of sun magic, able to control sunlight and create solar flares.

name: Baby Dragon (Ice)
description: This dragon is a master of ice magic, able to control blizzards and create ice storms.

name: Baby Dragon (Fire)
description: This dragon is a master of fire magic, able to control flames and create firestorms.

name: Baby Dragon (Obsidian)
description: This dragon is a master of obsidian magic, able to control shadows and create dark illusions.

name: Imposter Elite Royal Archer (Triple The Fun)
It's Been A Good Day Diner
